L2_gloss: First letter of the Georgian alphabet (Asomtavruli form). Its name is an ([ɑn]) and it is followed by Ⴁ (Ⴁ). It is the equivalent of the standard Mkhedruli form ა (a).
Second letter of the Georgian alphabet (Asomtavruli form). Its name is ban ([bɑn]) and it is preceded by Ⴀ (Ⴀ) and followed by Ⴂ (Ⴂ). It is the equivalent of the standard Mkhedruli form ბ (b).
Third letter of the Georgian alphabet (Asomtavruli form). Its name is gan ([ɡɑn]) and it is preceded by Ⴁ (Ⴁ) and followed by Ⴃ (Ⴃ). It is the equivalent of the standard Mkhedruli form გ (g).
Fourth letter of the Georgian alphabet (Asomtavruli form). Its name is don ([d̪ɔn]) and it is preceded by Ⴂ (Ⴂ) and followed by Ⴄ (Ⴄ). It is the equivalent of the standard Mkhedruli form დ (d).
Fifth letter of the Georgian alphabet (Asomtavruli form). Its name is en ([ɛn]) and it is preceded by Ⴃ and followed by Ⴅ. It is the equivalent of the standard Mkhedruli form ე (e).
Sixth letter of the Georgian alphabet (Asomtavruli form). Its name is vin ([vɪn]) and it is preceded by Ⴄ and followed by Ⴆ. It is the equivalent of the standard Mkhedruli form ვ (v).
Sixteenth letter of the Georgian alphabet (Asomtavruli form). Its name is on ([ɔn]) and it is preceded by Ⴢ and followed by Ⴎ. It is the equivalent of the standard Mkhedruli form ო (o).
First letter of the Georgian alphabet, transliterated as а. Its name is an and it is followed by ბ.
